{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_016KamaA14gsAaev2xQrBtJY","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is clear: the health check script on `mongodb-replica-1` is using a `health-user` credential that has a \"SCRAM authentication failed, storedKey mismatch\" error. This means the password stored in the `health-user-password` secret doesn't match what's stored in the MongoDB database for this pod.\n\nLet me look at:\n1. The health check script\n2. The health-user-password secret\n3. The health-overrides configmap\n4. What user exists on mongodb-replica-1\n\nThe error is \"SCRAM authentication failed, storedKey mismatch\" - this means the password in the secret doesn't match the one stored in MongoDB on this specific pod. This can happen when:\n- The pod was initialized with different credentials\n- The secret was changed after initialization\n\nI need to examine the health-check script and compare it against the secret to see what's actually being used.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":9208,"cache_read_input_tokens":29094,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":9208},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9dc4df6c-aac5-47cb-bd2f-6e919f6b931f","uuid":"15144709-64d0-4369-bc1f-213fa322aa4c","request_id":"req_011CcMXUM1ocrtVkPvBmfNG2"}
